SIMPLE: gimlet
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gimlet
<hw>Gim"let</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <altsp>[Also written and
pronounced <asp>gimbled</asp> <pr>(<?/)</pr>]</altsp> <ety>[OF.
<ets>guimbelet</ets>, <ets>guibelet</ets>, F. <ets>gibelet</ets>, prob.
fr. OD. <ets>wimpel</ets>, <ets>weme</ets>, a bore, <ets>wemelen</ets>
to bore, to wimble. See <er>Wimble</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>A
small tool for boring holes. It has a leading screw, a grooved body, and
a cross handle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Gimlet eye</b></col>, <cd>a squint-eye.</cd>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark> <au>Wright.</au></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gimlet</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Gimlet
<hw>Gim"let</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Gimleted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Gimleting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To pierce or make
with a gimlet.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>To turn round (an anchor) by the
stock, with a motion like turning a gimlet.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gimmal</ent>⟦br⟧
